user.biography: A Mexican Legacy. The true taste and beauty of the rich soil from the Tequila region, combined with the best agaves and a story of tradition.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Curamia Tequila in New York City, N.Y. with @curamiatequila. May be a black-and-white image of 1 person.

node.text:
Our journey begins many generations ago with the birth of Mexico’s most beautiful woman. A force for the terrain of its land and people. Her physical beauty paled in comparison to that of her heart. Many years later her truth has become mystery leading people on a search to understand the legacy she left behind.  LA MUJER MÁS BELLA 
Follow us on our journey

node.text:
The aromas of freshly grated citrus fruits and sun ripened earth open your palette to savor notes of fresh agave, pineapple and subtle notes of salted jalapeño. 
Why don’t you tell us what you think?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Curamia Tequila in New York City, N.Y.. May be an image of drink.

node.text: Curamia Tequila is as beautiful on the inside as it is on the out! Our process begins atop the Volcano of Tequila, when natural spring water trickles down the rugged cliffs to the underground wells below—natural aquifers, 70-meters beneath the earth’s surface. The volcanic soil enriches the water with essential minerals, which is harmonized with our tequila through a proprietary process. This combination of authenticity and craftsmanship, of heritage and innovation, is at the very heart of Curamia Tequila.
